odd davis also known as todd davis is the founder of lifelock a personal fraud protection company contents  education  career  other activities  philanthropy  recognition  references educationedit davis received his bachelor of business administration in entrepreneurship and management from baylor university in  careeredit davis served on executive management teams of several technology startups after graduating from baylor he later joined dell in  where he was able to sign clients such as m davis became a member of the president’s elite circle and received the dell vision award while with the company in  davis started his own business marketing champions where he served as ceo and worked with teams from nascar and the indy racing league in  davis and robert j maynard cofounded lifelock lifelock is a personal fraud protection company davis has served as the ceo of lifelock since its founding as part of a marketing campaign to raise public awareness to the threat of identity theft davis posted his social security number on billboards and commercials davis was a victim of  cases of identity theft between  and  the company ranked eighth on inc magazine’s  list in  and in  davis took the company public by  lifelock had over  million subscribers and  employees other activitiesedit davis is a regular speaker at conferences and other events in april  he was a speaker at the startup america summit in phoenix arizona the silicon desert december meetup and the company also presented a free identity theft summit for local law enforcement officials in arizona davis presented at the  south by southwest online privacy nuclear meltdown or nextgen fuel discussions he was selected to speak at the  global ethics summit and participated in the  inside the reporter’s notebook event for the phoenix business journal davis has contributed to forbes magazine and the huffington post with identity theft protection advice for individuals philanthropyedit davis through lifelock contributes to conquer paralysis now and serves on the board of directors the foundation founded in  works to find a cure for paralysis he is an honorary advisor the national organization for victim assistance as well as an honorary board member for bioaccel he’s also on the board of directors for the boys  girls club of greater phoenix recognitionedit davis won the ernst  young entrepreneur of the year for top emerging company for orange county and desert cities in  he was also awarded the crm magazines service elite award the arizona business leadership associations leadership award and arizona business journals  most admired ceos in  referencesedit  class action alleges deceptive marketing by lifelock  fraudprevention pitchman becomes id theft victim  cnncom  interview with todd davis ceo of lifelock  a b online privacy nuclear meltdown or nextgen fuel sxsw  retrieved march     a b lifelock inc bloomberg retrieved march     a b larry greenemeier january   high five meet todd davis ceo of lifelock information week retrieved march     a b lifelock’s todd davis building an awardwinning identity theft protection company corporate review october   retrieved march     how to proactively prevent identity theft internet scambusters retrieved march     david swartz   value investing challenge finalist pdf value investing challenge retrieved march     lifelock management lifelock retrieved march     fraudprevention pitchman becomes id theft victim  cnncom  cracking lifelock even after a  million penalty for deceptive advertising the tempe company cant be honest about its identitytheftprotection service  patrick ogrady august   lifelock tops among az firms on inc  phoenix business journal retrieved march     a b ilana lowery february   lifelock ceo shares more than ssn in first reporters notebook event phoenix business journal retrieved march     startup america summit speakers startup america summit  retrieved march     lifelock presents free identity theft summit to bring together law e