 is really going to be driven by the quality of the members were bringing on board and clearly a higher ltv member wed be willing to pay a higher coa so were always going to have a level of variability associated with coa kind of from a quartertoquarter basis based on the mix of the types of members were bringing on board but we would as we discussed with seeing the partner channel will take a little bit of time to fully return to the levels that weve seen and as a result since that is typically the lower cost of acquisition channel that will likely take us a few quarters to work through the system rob breza  wunderlich securities inc great thanks christopher g power  chief financial officer thank you operator there are no further questions at this time i would now like to turn the floor back over to todd davis for closing remarks please go ahead richard todd davis  chairman  chief executive officer thank you and i just want to thank everybody for joining us on the call and please feel free to visit our investor relations website at investorlifelockcom thank you very much for your time operator the conference has now concluded you may now disconnect your lines thank you for your participation copyright policy all transcripts on this site are the copyright of seeking alpha however we view them as an important resource for bloggers and journalists and are excited to contribute to the democratization of financial information on the internet until now investors have had to pay thousands of dollars in subscription fees for transcripts so our reproduction policy is as follows you may quote up to  words of any transcript on the condition that you attribute the transcript to seeking alpha and either link to the original transcript or to wwwseekingalphacom all other use is prohibited the information contained here is a textual representation of the applicable companys conference call conference presentation or other audio presentation and while efforts are made to provide an